snippet.textDisplay:
Excuse you that is executive dysfunction posing as procrastination. See also:


PROCRASTINATION:
Me: I reallllly don't want to do the thing but I need to
Brain: So lets do these other "really important" things and then get to it
Me: Okay!


EXECUTIVE DYSFUNCTION:
Me: We have this really important thing to do & now is the perfect opportunity so let's go!
Brain: No.
Me: E.....excuse me?
Brain: No. Let's not do the thing you so desperately want to do.
Me: Why not?
Brain: Because.
Me: Can we PLEASE go do the thing? PLEASE?? I really really want to do it!!
Brain: No.
Me: PLEASE??? I'm begging you. Let's go do the thing!
Brain: ............No.
Me: sigh okay.
